clientCache - Configures the client cache which is used by the controller to cache
(and potentially persist) vault tokens that are the result of using the VaultAuthMethod , what do they mean here by the VaultAuthMethod ?


VaultAuthMethod = the Authentication Method you configured

A VaultAuthMethod is how the operator authenticates to Vault to get a token. It corresponds to your VaultAuth CRD. For example:


apiVersion: secrets.hashicorp.com/v1beta1
kind: VaultAuth
metadata:
  name: my-k8s-auth
spec:
  type: kubernetes       # <-- VaultAuthMethod
  mountPath: kubernetes
  role: my-role
